JOHANNESBURG - More than 36 hours after the arrest of the two Gupta brothers, there is still no word on whether progress has been made in extraditing them to South Africa. Rajesh and Atul Gupta were arrested in Dubai on Monday, making headlines in South Africa and abroad. The arrests of two Gupta brothers this week has been lauded as a positive step in the country’s quest for accountability for state capture. ALSO READ:• Gupta arrests the start of a long process, warn legal experts• A great step forward: Outa, Casac laud arrest of Atul & Rajesh Gupta in UAE• Justice Dept working with UAE on way forward after Rajesh & Atul Gupta arrested• Justice Dept confirms Atul and Rajesh Gupta's arrest Fugitives from justice, Atul and Rajesh Gupta were arrested by law enforcement authorities in the United Arab Emirates. Corruption Watch said that they hoped that more arrests of senior officials and Gupta associates would now follow, along with a series of successful prosecutions. Many South Africans have been applauding the arrest of the two brothers after billions were taken in taxpayers' money but there is also widespread caution and speculation as to when or if the two will be brought to this country.